README.md
     1вҶ’# The only accessible & unstyled & full featured Input OTP component in the Web. вҖҰ
     3вҶ’### OTP Input for React рҹ”җ by [@guilhermerodz](https://twitter.com/guilherme_rodz)
    18вҶ’https://github.com/guilhermerodz/input-otp/assets/10366880/753751f5-eda8-4145-a4b9-7ef51ca5e453
    19вҶ’
    20вҶ’## Usage
    22вҶ’```bash
    23вҶ’npm install input-otp
    24вҶ’```
    25вҶ’
    26вҶ’Then import the component.
    27вҶ’
    28вҶ’```diff
    29вҶ’+'use client'
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    39вҶ’## Default example
    41вҶ’The example below uses `tailwindcss` `@shadcn/ui` `tailwind-merge` `clsx`:
    42вҶ’
    43вҶ’```tsx
    44вҶ’'use client'
    45вҶ’import { OTPInput, SlotProps } from 'input-otp'
    46вҶ’<OTPInput
    47вҶ’  maxLength={6}
    48вҶ’  containerClassName="group flex items-center has-[:disabled]:opacity-30"
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   136вҶ’## How it works
   138вҶ’There's currently no native OTP/2FA/MFA input in HTML, which means people are either going with 1. a simple input design or 2. custom designs like this one.
   139вҶ’This library works by rendering an invisible input as a sibling of the slots, contained by a `relative`ly positioned parent (the container root called _OTPInput_).
   140вҶ’
   141вҶ’## Features
   143вҶ’This is the most complete OTP input on the web. It's fully featured 
   144вҶ’
   145вҶ’<details>
   146вҶ’<summary>Supports iOS + Android copy-paste-cut</summary>
   147вҶ’
   148вҶ’https://github.com/guilhermerodz/input-otp/assets/10366880/bdbdc96a-23da-4e89-bff8-990e6a1c4c23
   149вҶ’
   150вҶ’</details>
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   198вҶ’### Auto tracks if the input has space in the right side for the badge
   200вҶ’https://github.com/guilhermerodz/input-otp/assets/10366880/bf01af88-1f82-463e-adf4-54a737a92f59
   201вҶ’
   202вҶ’</details>
   203вҶ’
   204вҶ’## API Reference
   206вҶ’### OTPInput
   208вҶ’The root container. Define settings for the input via props. Then, use the `render` prop to create the slots.
   209вҶ’
   210вҶ’#### Props
   212вҶ’```ts
   213вҶ’type OTPInputProps = {
   214вҶ’  // The number of slots
   215вҶ’  maxLength: number
   216вҶ’
   217вҶ’  // Render function creating the slots
   218вҶ’  render: (props: RenderProps) => React.ReactElement
      вҶ’вҖҰ
